      "message": "I think we need to allow for target-implemented alignment buffers; for example the as3525 uses an uncacheable address for its internal realignment buffer.  With this patch as-is, we\u0027ll realign twice,\n\nAlternatively, perhaps we could call this STORAGE_WANTS_ALIGN_GENERIC to show that we want to use this buffer vs everything getting properly fixed up in the target driver?\n\nAlso, outside of target-specific code, the only actual user of the WANTS_ALIGN macros is in apps.buffering.c -- I wonder if that special casing might actually be superfluous in light of this patch?  Or perhaps this patch is actually slower/less optimal than how the buffering handles things?",
